    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PHILIPPINES CUTS PHONE RATES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Wayne Arnold</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Arnold, Wayne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co, responding to competition, makes deep cuts in charges for calls to US and nine other countries; calls to US will fall to minimum of 49 cents a minute from more than $1 a minute (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Responding to competition, the Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company made deep cuts in charges for calls to the United States and nine other countries. Calls to the United States will fall to a minimum of 49 cents a minute from more than $1 a minute. Declining international calls have been sapping the company's revenue, worsening financial problems caused by losses at its cellular subsidiary and the cost of absorbing a former cellular rival.</p>
        <p>Wayne Arnold (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Responding to competition, the Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company made deep cuts in charges for calls to the United States and nine other countries. Calls to the United States will fall to a minimum of 49 cents a minute from more than $1 a minute. Declining international calls have been sapping the company's revenue, worsening financial problems caused by losses at its cellular subsidiary and the cost of absorbing a former cellular rival.</p>
